       copy device or a graphics monitor. Output can include a raster map, any
       number  of  vector overlays, site data, text labels, and other map ele-
       ments.

       This command has  three  modes  of  operation.  The  command-line  mode
       requires  a previously prepared file of mapping instructions describing
       the map elements to be printed. The interactive mode (i.e., no command-
       line  arguments)  will  prompt the user for items to be mapped and does
       not require the user to prepare a file of  instructions.  The  keyboard
       mode is started by entering a hyphen ( - ) for the iinnppuutt parameter. The
       _p_._m_a_p_._n_e_w instructions would then be entered via the keyboard.

